snippet.textDisplay: Never watched this channel before, probably wont again. I'm shocked just how little everyone knows about engineering. Why would you think those HUGE holes in pegboard is the right way to go? You need pressure, not flow. That's why an air hockey table has very tiny holes in it. Also, you don't need a light puck, you need a heavy puck so it can maintain momentum. An air hockey puck is pretty heavy for its size. It's heavier by its self than most of the things you tried. Have you ever watched videos of the military hovercraft? It weighs thousands of pounds and floats on air. Air is more powerful than you think and it doesn't take much to make something float.
